=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: N-Boc-4-piperidone → protect the ketone as the ethylene ketal with HOCH2CH2OH, cat. p-TsOH (water removal) to give N-Boc-1,4-dioxa-8-azaspiro[4.5]decane | Step 2: α-Lithiation of this N-Boc spiroketal (LDA), then quench with formaldehyde/paraformaldehyde to form N-Boc-2-(hydroxymethyl)-1,4-dioxa-8-azaspiro[4.5]decane | Step 3: Convert the alcohol to a leaving group, e.g. PBr3 or MsCl/Et3N, to give N-Boc-2-(bromomethyl)- or 2-(mesyloxymethyl)-1,4-dioxa-8-azaspiro[4.5]decane | Step 4: SN2 displacement with piperidine (DMF or MeCN, base such as K2CO3/DIPEA) to give N-Boc-2-(piperidin-1-ylmethyl)-1,4-dioxa-8-azaspiro[4.5]decane | Step 5: Remove Boc from the spirocyclic nitrogen with TFA/CH2Cl2 or HCl/dioxane to furnish the target C1CCN(CC2CC3(CCN2)OCCO3)C1.

